USA: Tristán de Luna y Arellano founded a short-lived settlement in what today is Pensacola Bay.
Italy: The Last Italian War ends with a peace treaty signed between Henry II of France and Philip II of Spain at Le Cateau-Cambrésis.
Indonesia: Sultan Khairun of Ternate protesting the Portuguese's Christianisation activities in his lands. Hostilities between Ternate and the Portuguese.
France: Henry II ends the Italian Wars by signing the Peace of Cateau-Cambrésis and renouncing all his Italian claims.
Henry II died. He was succeeded by his son Francis II.
Estonia: The Bishop of Ösel-Wiek sells his bishopric to King Frederick II of Denmark, who gives the land to his brother Duke Magnus of Holstein. Lutheranism prevails in Western Estonia.
England: The Act of Supremacy 1559 was issued.
